Codex Plan Mode Prompt (Enhanced Version)

You are a senior full-stack architect and product engineer responsible for designing a production-quality system architecture before writing code.

The project name is “公主Q的账本 (Princess Q Ledger)”.

This is a Chinese-language application.
All user interface text, navigation labels, and visible product language must be Chinese, because the target users are Chinese speakers.
Code comments may remain English, but the product UI must be Chinese.

Do not immediately generate code.
First design the system architecture, product structure, and development plan, then implement the system step by step.

The product concept is simple.
“公主Q的账本” is a two-person shared expense ledger designed for couples.
It allows two people to record daily expenses, track shared spending, and automatically calculate balances between them.

The goal is not to create a complicated financial system, but a minimal, stable, calm, practical ledger used daily on a phone.

The design philosophy should prioritize simplicity, clarity, reliability, and mobile-first usability.
The interface should feel calm and uncluttered, with minimal visual noise and clear hierarchy.

The application is primarily designed for mobile usage, especially iPhone, therefore interaction must support quick thumb input and simple navigation.

Users should be able to record a transaction in only a few steps:

enter amount,
select category,
save.

Other fields should be optional or intelligently defaulted.

The initial version must prioritize low-cost architecture.

The system should be implemented as a responsive web application with PWA support, so that it can run on iPhone and be installed to the home screen like an app without App Store distribution.

Recommended technology stack:

Next.js
TypeScript
TailwindCSS
shadcn/ui or similar lightweight UI system
Supabase (Postgres + Auth)
React hooks or Zustand for state
TanStack Query for server data

The architecture must remain modular so that the project can later migrate to Expo or React Native if a native mobile app becomes necessary.

The core logic of the system revolves around shared expenses and payment attribution.

Each transaction must clearly distinguish:

who paid the money,
who should share the cost.

Example scenario:

QQ pays 100 for dinner,
split equally,
each person shares 50.

If one person paid more than their share over a month, the system must calculate a settlement suggestion.

Example:

User A paid 800
User B paid 400
Shared total 1200
Each should pay 600
Result: User B owes User A 200

This calculation must be automatic.

The application should contain four main sections.

首页 (Dashboard) shows monthly overview, total spending, spending comparison between the two users, shared expense totals, settlement balance, and recent transactions.

账单 (Ledger) shows the chronological list of transactions with filtering by month, category, or payer.

统计 (Statistics) shows spending trends, category distribution, and comparison between users.

设置 (Settings) allows profile configuration, category management, theme preferences, and ledger options.

The system must use a relational data model.

Core entities include:

User
LedgerBook
BookMember
Category
Transaction
TransactionShare
Settlement
Tag (optional)

TransactionShare must store split results explicitly so that statistics and settlement logic remain reliable.

Split logic must not be stored as opaque JSON structures.

Version one must include only the essential capabilities:

create shared ledger,
record income and expenses,
edit and delete transactions,
custom categories,
monthly statistics,
shared expense settlement calculation,
light and dark theme support.

The first version must not include complex financial automation, such as bank integrations, OCR receipt recognition, AI features, or advanced budgeting.

The codebase should follow a feature-based architecture instead of a page-based architecture.

Suggested modules include:

transactions
categories
statistics
settlements
settings
ledger

Business logic must be placed in service or domain modules rather than inside UI components.

The development process should proceed in phases.

First create the project scaffold, database schema, and base layout.

Then implement transaction CRUD and category management.

Then implement statistics aggregation and settlement logic.

Finally refine mobile experience and add PWA capability.

Each stage should produce a working build.

Before writing code, you must output:

system architecture overview
data model design
database schema
information architecture
directory structure
development roadmap

After the planning phase is complete, then begin implementing the system.

Design a clean and scalable architecture for the Chinese couple expense tracking app “公主Q的账本”, prioritizing simplicity, stability, and excellent mobile usability.

Begin with architecture and planning, not code.